Package: CorHeat
Type: Package
Title: Integrate The correlation analysis of omics with r and P cutoff values, and draw heatmaps with significant markers
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:person(given="Lanlan",family="Zhao",email="lanlan_z@mail.sdu.edu.cn",role = c('aut','cre'))
Maintainer: The package maintainer <yourself@somewhere.net>
Description: More about what it does (maybe more than one line)
    Computes a matrix of Spearman's rho or Pearson's r rank correlation coefficients for all possible pairs of columns of a matrix, filter based on the threshold of P and r cutoff, and output the matrix.
    Draw clustered heatmaps with Significant markers.
